<h2 id="intro">Introduction</h2>
<p>
  <strong>Not implemented.</strong> The Nimbus runtime speaks a single JSON POST/response cycle per action. There is no chunked streaming channel or SSE bridge in the stock plugin.
</p>

<h2 id="basic-usage">Basic usage</h2>
<p><em>Not available.</em> For long-running jobs, poll with <code>wire:poll</code>, use a WebSocket solution outside this plugin, or push status through a separate API.</p>

<h2 id="common-use-cases">Common use cases</h2>
<h3>LLM tokens</h3>
<p>Buffer output server-side and flush partial results by storing ciphertext or deltas in state, then sync with <code>wire:poll</code>—or integrate Transmit/another realtime layer.</p>

<h2 id="reference">Reference</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Status:</strong> not implemented.</li>
  <li><strong>Reason:</strong> response model today is one JSON payload with HTML + state.</li>
</ul>
